  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-n-sticky-mongolian-style-tofu-and-tenderstem-with-rice/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Drain your <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, crumble the <strong>tofu </strong>roughly into the pan with your hands</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> cook for 6-7 min or until golden and crispy – this is your <strong>crispy tofu</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-n-sticky-mongolian-style-tofu-and-tenderstem-with-rice/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> Tenderstem broccoli </strong>in half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-n-sticky-mongolian-style-tofu-and-tenderstem-with-rice/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped Tenderstem</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 2-3 min or until the Tenderstem is tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-n-sticky-mongolian-style-tofu-and-tenderstem-with-rice/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>cornflour </strong>and <strong>umami seasoning </strong>with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[220ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>in a small bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>tamarind paste </strong>and <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and stir it all together – this is your <strong>sweet 'n' sticky sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-n-sticky-mongolian-style-tofu-and-tenderstem-with-rice/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tofu is golden and crisp, add the <strong>sweet 'n' sticky sauce </strong>and <strong>cooked Tenderstem</strong>,<strong> </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>sweet 'n' sticky Mongolian-style tofu & Tenderstem</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-n-sticky-mongolian-style-tofu-and-tenderstem-with-rice/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>cooked white long grain rice </strong>to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-n-sticky-mongolian-style-tofu-and-tenderstem-with-rice/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sweet 'n' sticky Mongolian-style tofu & Tenderstem </strong>over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>black sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
